Note:
Enhanced Lexer Tests: Comprehensive Test Suite

This test suite validates the enhanced lexer implementation with:
- Edge case handling
- Performance optimization
- Error recovery strategies
- Large file processing
- Memory usage optimization
:End Note

Note: Import test dependencies
Import "../../../src/compiler/lexer/lexer.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/lexer/token.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/lexer/diagnostics.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/lexer/internal/definitions.runa"
Import "../../../src/compiler/lexer/internal/utilities.runa"

Note: Test Suite Configuration
Let test_config be dictionary containing:
    "verbose" as true
    "performance_tracking" as true
    "memory_tracking" as true
    "max_test_time_ms" as 5000

Note: Test Results Tracking
Let test_results be dictionary containing:
    "total_tests" as 0
    "passed_tests" as 0
    "failed_tests" as 0
    "performance_tests" as 0
    "edge_case_tests" as 0
    "error_recovery_tests" as 0

Note: Test Helper Functions
Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Note: Run a single test with performance tracking
    Set test_results.total_tests to test_results.total_tests plus 1
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
    Let result be test_function
    Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
    Let duration be end_time minus start_time
    
    If result:
        Set test_results.passed_tests to test_results.passed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Display "✅ PASS: " plus test_name plus " (" plus duration plus "ms)"
    Otherwise:
        Set test_results.failed_tests to test_results.failed_tests plus 1
        If test_config.verbose:
            Display "❌ FAIL: " plus test_name plus " (" plus duration plus "ms)"
    
    If duration is greater than test_config.max_test_time_ms:
        Display "⚠️  SLOW: " plus test_name plus " took " plus duration plus "ms"
    
    Return result

Process called "run_performance_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Note: Run a performance-focused test
    Set test_results.performance_tests to test_results.performance_tests plus 1
    Return run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function

Process called "run_edge_case_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Note: Run an edge case test
    Set test_results.edge_case_tests to test_results.edge_case_tests plus 1
    Return run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function

Process called "run_error_recovery_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Note: Run an error recovery test
    Set test_results.error_recovery_tests to test_results.error_recovery_tests plus 1
    Return run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function

Note: Basic Functionality Tests
Process called "test_basic_tokenization" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test basic tokenization functionality
    Let source be "Let x be 42"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is equal to 5 and
           tokens at index 0.type is equal to IDENTIFIER and
           tokens at index 1.type is equal to IDENTIFIER and
           tokens at index 2.type is equal to IDENTIFIER and
           tokens at index 3.type is equal to INTEGER_LITERAL and
           tokens at index 4.type is equal to EOF

Process called "test_multi_word_constructs" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test multi-word construct recognition
    Let source be "x is greater than y and z is less than w"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let multi_word_count be 0
    For each token in tokens:
        If token.type is equal to MULTI_WORD_CONSTRUCT:
            Set multi_word_count to multi_word_count plus 1
    
    Return multi_word_count is greater than 0

Process called "test_case_insensitive_keywords" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test case-insensitive keyword recognition
    Let source be "LET x BE 42\nIF x IS GREATER THAN 10"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let keyword_count be 0
    For each token in tokens:
        If token.type is equal to IDENTIFIER and (token.normalized_value is equal to "let" or token.normalized_value is equal to "be" or token.normalized_value is equal to "if"):
            Set keyword_count to keyword_count plus 1
    
    Return keyword_count is greater than 0

Note: Edge Case Tests
Process called "test_extremely_long_strings" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test handling of extremely long strings
    Let long_string be "\"" plus (repeat_string with text as "a" and count as 10000) plus "\""
    Let source be "Let x be " plus long_string
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0 and
           tokens at index (length of tokens minus 1).type is equal to EOF

Process called "test_nested_multi_word_constructs" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test nested multi-word constructs
    Let source be "if x is greater than y and z is less than w or a is equal to b"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let multi_word_count be 0
    For each token in tokens:
        If token.type is equal to MULTI_WORD_CONSTRUCT:
            Set multi_word_count to multi_word_count plus 1
    
    Return multi_word_count is greater than 2

Process called "test_complex_number_literals" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test complex number literal formats
    Let source be "Let x be 0x1A2B3C4D\nLet y be 0b10101010\nLet z be 0o1234567\nLet w be 1_234_567\nLet v be 3.14159e-10"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let number_count be 0
    For each token in tokens:
        If token.type is equal to INTEGER_LITERAL or token.type is equal to FLOAT_LITERAL:
            Set number_count to number_count plus 1
    
    Return number_count is equal to 5

Process called "test_unicode_escape_sequences" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test Unicode escape sequence handling
    Let source be "Let x be \"Hello \\u{1F600} World\""
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0 and
           tokens at index (length of tokens minus 1).type is equal to EOF

Process called "test_mixed_case_identifiers" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test mixed case identifier handling
    Let source be "Let UserName be \"John\"\nLet user_age be 25\nLet USER_ID be 12345"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let identifier_count be 0
    For each token in tokens:
        If token.type is equal to IDENTIFIER or token.type is equal to QUALIFIED_IDENTIFIER:
            Set identifier_count to identifier_count plus 1
    
    Return identifier_count is greater than 3

Process called "test_deep_indentation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test deep indentation handling
    Let source be "if x is greater than 0:\n    if y is greater than 0:\n        if z is greater than 0:\n            Let result be true"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let indent_count be 0
    Let dedent_count be 0
    For each token in tokens:
        If token.type is equal to INDENT:
            Set indent_count to indent_count plus 1
        Otherwise if token.type is equal to DEDENT:
            Set dedent_count to dedent_count plus 1
    
    Return indent_count is greater than 0 and dedent_count is greater than 0

Note: Performance Tests
Process called "test_large_file_performance" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test performance with large files
    Let large_source be ""
    For i from 1 to 1000:
        Set large_source to large_source plus "Let variable" plus i plus " be " plus i plus "\n"
    
    Let start_time be get_current_time_ms
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as large_source and file_path as "large_test.runa"
    Let end_time be get_current_time_ms
    Let duration be end_time minus start_time
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 3000 and duration is less than 1000

Process called "test_memory_usage_optimization" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test memory usage optimization
    Let source be "Let x be 42\nLet y be \"Hello World\"\nLet z be true"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let memory_usage be estimate_memory_usage with tokens as tokens
    
    Return memory_usage is greater than 0 and memory_usage is less than 1000

Process called "test_streaming_mode_activation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test streaming mode activation for large files
    Let large_source be repeat_string with text as "Let x be 42\n" and count as 50000
    
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as large_source and file_path as "streaming_test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 100000

Note: Error Recovery Tests
Process called "test_unterminated_string_recovery" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test recovery from unterminated strings
    Let source be "Let x be \"Hello World\nLet y be 42"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0 and
           tokens at index (length of tokens minus 1).type is equal to EOF

Process called "test_invalid_escape_sequence_recovery" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test recovery from invalid escape sequences
    Let source be "Let x be \"Hello \\k World\"\nLet y be 42"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0 and
           tokens at index (length of tokens minus 1).type is equal to EOF

Process called "test_unexpected_character_recovery" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test recovery from unexpected characters
    Let source be "Let x be 42\nLet y be @invalid\nLet z be 100"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0 and
           tokens at index (length of tokens minus 1).type is equal to EOF

Process called "test_malformed_number_recovery" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test recovery from malformed numbers
    Let source be "Let x be 0xG\nLet y be 0b2\nLet z be 0o9\nLet w be 42"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0 and
           tokens at index (length of tokens minus 1).type is equal to EOF

Note: Advanced Edge Case Tests
Process called "test_complex_nested_structures" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test complex nested structures
    Let source be "if x is greater than y and (z is less than w or a is equal to b) and not (c is greater than d):\n    Let result be true\n    if nested is true:\n        Let nested_result be false"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 20

Process called "test_mixed_syntax_styles" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test mixed syntax styles
    Let source be "Let x be 42\nIf x is greater than 10:\n    Display \"Large number\"\nOtherwise:\n    Display \"Small number\""
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 15

Process called "test_extreme_whitespace_handling" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test extreme whitespace handling
    Let source be "    Let    x    be    42    \n\n\n    If    x    is    greater    than    10    :\n        Let    result    be    true"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0

Process called "test_comment_edge_cases" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test comment edge cases
    Let source be "Note: This is a comment\nLet x be 42\nNote:\nThis is a\nmulti-line comment\n:End Note\nLet y be 100"
    Let tokens be tokenize with source_code as source and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Return length of tokens is greater than 0

Note: Utility Function Tests
Process called "test_hex_digit_validation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test hex digit validation
    Return is_hex_digit with char as "0" and
           is_hex_digit with char as "9" and
           is_hex_digit with char as "a" and
           is_hex_digit with char as "f" and
           is_hex_digit with char as "A" and
           is_hex_digit with char as "F" and
           not is_hex_digit with char as "g" and
           not is_hex_digit with char as "G"

Process called "test_identifier_validation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test identifier validation
    Return is_identifier_start with char as "a" and
           is_identifier_start with char as "Z" and
           is_identifier_start with char as "_" and
           not is_identifier_start with char as "0" and
           not is_identifier_start with char as "!" and
           is_identifier_continue with char as "a" and
           is_identifier_continue with char as "0" and
           not is_identifier_continue with char as "!"

Process called "test_boolean_literal_detection" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test boolean literal detection
    Return is_boolean_literal with text as "true" and
           is_boolean_literal with text as "false" and
           is_boolean_literal with text as "TRUE" and
           is_boolean_literal with text as "FALSE" and
           is_boolean_literal with text as "True" and
           is_boolean_literal with text as "False" and
           not is_boolean_literal with text as "yes" and
           not is_boolean_literal with text as "no"

Note: Main Test Runner
Process called "run_all_enhanced_lexer_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Run all enhanced lexer tests
    Display "🧪 Running Enhanced Lexer Test Suite..."
    Display ""
    
    Note: Basic functionality tests
    Let basic_tests be list containing:
        "Basic Tokenization" as test_basic_tokenization
        "Multi-word Constructs" as test_multi_word_constructs
        "Case Insensitive Keywords" as test_case_insensitive_keywords
    
    For each test_name and test_function in basic_tests:
        run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function
    
    Display ""
    Display "🔍 Running Edge Case Tests..."
    
    Note: Edge case tests
    Let edge_case_tests be list containing:
        "Extremely Long Strings" as test_extremely_long_strings
        "Nested Multi-word Constructs" as test_nested_multi_word_constructs
        "Complex Number Literals" as test_complex_number_literals
        "Unicode Escape Sequences" as test_unicode_escape_sequences
        "Mixed Case Identifiers" as test_mixed_case_identifiers
        "Deep Indentation" as test_deep_indentation
        "Complex Nested Structures" as test_complex_nested_structures
        "Mixed Syntax Styles" as test_mixed_syntax_styles
        "Extreme Whitespace Handling" as test_extreme_whitespace_handling
        "Comment Edge Cases" as test_comment_edge_cases
    
    For each test_name and test_function in edge_case_tests:
        run_edge_case_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function
    
    Display ""
    Display "⚡ Running Performance Tests..."
    
    Note: Performance tests
    Let performance_tests be list containing:
        "Large File Performance" as test_large_file_performance
        "Memory Usage Optimization" as test_memory_usage_optimization
        "Streaming Mode Activation" as test_streaming_mode_activation
    
    For each test_name and test_function in performance_tests:
        run_performance_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function
    
    Display ""
    Display "🛠️  Running Error Recovery Tests..."
    
    Note: Error recovery tests
    Let error_recovery_tests be list containing:
        "Unterminated String Recovery" as test_unterminated_string_recovery
        "Invalid Escape Sequence Recovery" as test_invalid_escape_sequence_recovery
        "Unexpected Character Recovery" as test_unexpected_character_recovery
        "Malformed Number Recovery" as test_malformed_number_recovery
    
    For each test_name and test_function in error_recovery_tests:
        run_error_recovery_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function
    
    Display ""
    Display "🔧 Running Utility Function Tests..."
    
    Note: Utility function tests
    Let utility_tests be list containing:
        "Hex Digit Validation" as test_hex_digit_validation
        "Identifier Validation" as test_identifier_validation
        "Boolean Literal Detection" as test_boolean_literal_detection
    
    For each test_name and test_function in utility_tests:
        run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function
    
    Display ""
    Display "📊 Test Results Summary:"
    Display "   Total Tests: " plus test_results.total_tests
    Display "   Passed: " plus test_results.passed_tests
    Display "   Failed: " plus test_results.failed_tests
    Display "   Performance Tests: " plus test_results.performance_tests
    Display "   Edge Case Tests: " plus test_results.edge_case_tests
    Display "   Error Recovery Tests: " plus test_results.error_recovery_tests
    
    Let success_rate be (test_results.passed_tests divided by test_results.total_tests) multiplied by 100
    
    Display "   Success Rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    
    If success_rate is greater than or equal to 95:
        Display "🎉 Enhanced Lexer Test Suite PASSED!"
    Otherwise:
        Display "❌ Enhanced Lexer Test Suite FAILED!"
    
    Return test_results

Note: Test Execution
Let results be run_all_enhanced_lexer_tests with 